{"title_page": "Krosno Odrza\u0144skie County", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=[[Krosno County]], which has the same name in Polish}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Krosno Odrza\u0144skie County\n| native_name = Powiat kro\u015bnie\u0144ski\n| settlement_type = [[Powiat|County]]\n| total_type = Total\n| image_flag = POL powiat kro\u015bnie\u0144ski (lubuski) flag.svg\n| image_shield = POL powiat kro\u015bnie\u0144ski (lubuski) COA.svg\n| image_map = Woj lubuskie powiat krosnienski.svg\n| map_caption = Location within the voivodeship\n| subdivision_type = Country\n| subdivision_name = {{POL}}\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Voivodeships of Poland|Voivodeship]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Lubusz Voivodeship|Lubusz]]\n| area_total_km2 = 1390\n| population_as_of = 2019-06-30<ref>{{cite web |title=Population. Size and structure and vital statistics in Poland by territorial divison in 2019. As of 30th June|url=https://stat.gov.pl/en/topics/population/population/population-size-and-structure-and-vital-statistics-in-poland-by-territorial-divison-in-2019-as-of-30th-june,3,26.html|website=stat.gov.pl|publisher=Statistics Poland|date=2019-10-15|accessdate=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n| population_total = 55018\n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| population_urban = 27938\n| population_blank1_title = Rural\n| population_blank1 = 27080\n| coor_pinpoint = Krosno Odrza\u0144skie\n| coordinates = {{coord|52|2|N|15|6|E|region:PL|display=inline,title}}\n| seat = [[Krosno Odrza\u0144skie]]\n| parts_type = [[Gmina]]s\n| parts = Total 7 (incl. 1 urban)\n| p1 = [[Gubin, Poland|Gubin]]\n| p2 = [[Gmina Bobrowice]]\n| p3 = [[Gmina Bytnica]]\n| p4 = [[Gmina D\u0105bie, Lubusz Voivodeship|Gmina D\u0105bie]]\n| p5 = [[Gmina Gubin]]\n| p6 = [[Gmina Krosno Odrza\u0144skie]]\n| p7 = [[Gmina Maszewo, Lubusz Voivodeship|Gmina Maszewo]]\n| blank_name = [[Polish car number plates|Car plates]]\n| blank_info = FKR\n| website = http://www.pow.krosno-odrz.pl }}\n__NOTOC__\n'''Krosno Odrza\u0144skie County''' ({{lang-pl|powiat kro\u015bnie\u0144ski}}) is a unit of territorial administration and local government ([[powiat]]) in [[Lubusz Voivodeship]], western [[Poland]], on the [[Germany|German]] border. It came into being on January 1, 1999, as a result of the [[Polish local government reforms]] passed in 1998. Its administrative seat is the town of [[Krosno Odrza\u0144skie]], which lies {{convert|30|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} west of [[Zielona G\u00f3ra]] and {{convert|79|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south of [[Gorz\u00f3w Wielkopolski]]. The only other town in the county is [[Gubin, Poland|Gubin]], situated on the German border {{convert|28|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} west of Krosno Odrza\u0144skie.\n\nThe county covers an area of {{convert|1390|km2|sqmi|1}}. As of 2019 its total population is 55,018, out of which the population of Gubin is 16,619, that of Krosno Odrza\u0144skie is 11,319, and the rural population is 27,080.\n\nSome of it's residence speak German.\n\n==Neighbouring counties==\nKrosno Odrza\u0144skie County is bordered by [[S\u0142ubice County]] to the north-west, [[Sul\u0119cin County]] to the north, [[\u015awiebodzin County]] to the north-east, [[Zielona G\u00f3ra County]] to the east and [[\u017bary County]] to the south. It also borders [[Brandenburg]] in [[Germany]] to the west.\n\n==Administrative division==\nThe county is subdivided into seven [[gmina]]s (one urban, one urban-rural and five rural). These are listed in the following table, in descending order of population.\n\n{| width=\"60%\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"font-size:90%;line-height:120%;\"\n|-bgcolor=\"F0F8FF\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Gmina'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Type'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Area<br><small>(km\u00b2)</small>'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Population<br><small>(2019)</small>'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Seat'''\n|-\n|[[Gmina Krosno Odrza\u0144skie]]\n|urban-rural\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"|211.5\n| style=\"text-align:righ